cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the delivery time of a wireless network under finite precision channel state information. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper investigates the impact of cache resources on reducing file delivery latency in a wireless network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper studies the performance of a cache-aided broadcast-relay wireless network and derives bounds on the worst-case per-bit latency. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with the distribution of storage resources in the form of caches in a wireless network. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on multimedia content specifically, but rather on the delivery time of files in general.
